# ARCH-003

# JOE INDUSTRIES Cloud & License Architecture

Version: 2.0

Status: OFFICIAL

This document supersedes all previous versions of ARCH-003.

---

# 1. Purpose

The JOE INDUSTRIES Cloud platform is NOT an ERP system.

It is an internal management platform used only by JOE INDUSTRIES.

Its primary purpose in Version 1 is License Management.

The Cloud platform SHALL NOT contain student data, grades, financial records or school operational data.

---

# 2. Cloud Responsibilities (Version 1)

The Cloud platform is responsible ONLY for:

- Schools Management
- License Management
- Device Registration
- License Validation
- Company User Accounts
- Basic Dashboard

The following features are postponed to future versions:

- Automatic Updates
- Cloud Backup
- Remote Support
- Analytics
- Marketplace

---

# 3. Technology Stack

Version 1 shall use:

Frontend

- Next.js

Authentication

- Firebase Authentication

Database

- Cloud Firestore

Hosting

- Vercel

License API

- Firebase Cloud Functions

No dedicated VPS is required.

No paid cloud infrastructure is required.

The system must remain compatible with future migration to another cloud provider.

---

# 4. Communication

The ERP Server SHALL NEVER connect directly to Firestore.

Communication must always follow this architecture:

ERP Server

↓

HTTPS

↓

Firebase Cloud Function

↓

Firestore

Direct database access from ERP Server is prohibited.

---

# 5. Authentication

Only JOE INDUSTRIES employees can sign in.

Supported roles:

- Administrator
- Support
- Sales

Schools cannot log into the Cloud Platform.

---

# 6. School Information

Only business information is stored.

Example:

- School ID
- School Name
- City
- Package
- License ID
- Status
- Expiry Date
- Maximum Devices

No academic information is stored.

---

# 7. License

Each school owns one License.

Each License contains:

- License ID
- License Key
- School ID
- Package
- Status
- Expiry Date
- Activation Date
- Maximum Devices

---

# 8. Device Registration

Each ERP Server owns one unique Device ID.

During activation:

License Key

↓

Cloud Function

↓

Validation

↓

Device Registration

↓

Activation Success

A License may only be activated on authorized devices.

---

# 9. Monthly Validation

Every 30 days the ERP Server SHALL attempt to validate the License.

Validation request contains only:

- License Key
- Device ID
- ERP Version

No school data is transmitted.

If validation succeeds:

The next validation date is updated.

If Internet is unavailable:

The ERP Server continues operating normally.

---

# 10. Grace Period

If validation cannot be completed after the scheduled period:

The system enters Grace Mode.

During Grace Mode:

- Full operation continues.
- Warning messages are displayed.

After Grace Mode expires:

Blocked:

- Creating new records
- Synchronization
- Future cloud services

Still allowed:

- Login
- Search
- Reports
- Printing
- Viewing existing data

---

# 11. Updates

Version 1 does NOT include automatic updates.

System updates are installed manually by JOE INDUSTRIES.

---

# 12. Backup

Cloud Backup is NOT implemented in Version 1.

Schools use:

- Local Backup
- External Drive Backup

Cloud Backup will be added in a future release.

---

# 13. Dashboard

The Cloud Dashboard displays:

- Total Schools
- Active Licenses
- Expired Licenses
- Registered Devices
- Packages
- Company Users

No school operational data is displayed.

---

# 14. Security Rules

ERP Server never accesses Firestore directly.

All validation passes through Cloud Functions.

All requests use HTTPS.

All operations are logged.

Student information is never uploaded.

---

# 15. Future Expansion

Future versions may include:

- Automatic Updates
- Cloud Backup
- Remote Support
- Analytics
- Notifications
- Multi-Branch Management

These features are intentionally excluded from Version 1.

---

# End of ARCH-003 Version 2.0
